Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Parents, Teens and the Culture of Sex: The Claims of Parenting
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b017x0vm
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 12 Dec 2011
Laurie Taylor examines research into the advice offered to parents with Judith Suissa from the Institute of Education and Frank Furedi from Kent University and looks at comparative research in America and Holland into teenage sex in the parental home with sociologist Amy Schalet from the University of Massachusetts. Producer: Chris Wilson. Show less